# Per-agent launchd config consumed by render.sh.
#
# Format: each non-comment, non-blank line is a record with up to six
# tab-separated fields:
#
#   1. label       - launchd job label (also the .plist filename stem)
#   2. script      - python file in HERMES_HOME/bin/ to invoke
#   3. schedule    - one of:
#                      interval:<seconds>
#                      cron:<HH>:<MM>                 (daily)
#                      cron:<weekday>:<HH>:<MM>       (weekly; 0=Sun)
#   4. needs_java  - "yes" or "no". "yes" prepends openjdk@21 + fnm
#                    bins to PATH and sets JAVA_HOME. Set this for any
#                    agent whose claude -p might compile Kotlin or invoke
#                    Node tooling that fnm pins.
#   5. log_stem    - basename used for /tmp/<stem>.{stdout,stderr}.
#                    Empty falls back to label. Useful when two plists
#                    share a script (sso-check-10 and sso-check-22 both
#                    write to /tmp/luminik.eng.sso-check.{stdout,stderr}).
#   6. role        - one-line operational descriptor in plain English.
#                    Surfaced in `alfred agents`, `alfred status <agent>`,
#                    and Slack post prefixes — codenames alone don't
#                    carry meaning to a fresh contributor (or to your
#                    future self at 2am). Keep it under ~50 chars.
#                    Optional but strongly recommended.
#
# Tabs are required between fields. Trailing empty fields can be omitted.

# Example entries. Replace with your own codenames.
#
# A scheduler-style codename that polls every 20 minutes:
#   my.fleet.poller	poller.py	interval:1200	yes			Issue poller
#
# A nightly reviewer that runs at 02:00:
#   my.fleet.reviewer	reviewer.py	cron:2:00	yes			Nightly PR reviewer
#
# A weekly Sunday-night dependency scanner at 22:00:
#   my.fleet.deps	deps-scanner.py	cron:0:22:00	yes			Weekly dependency audit
#
# A check that fires at 10:00 AND 22:00 (two rows, shared script + log_stem):
#   my.fleet.health-am	health-check.py	cron:10:00	no	my.fleet.health	Fleet health (morning)
#   my.fleet.health-pm	health-check.py	cron:22:00	no	my.fleet.health	Fleet health (evening)
